Deputy President William Ruto (pictured) yesterday left for Bamako, Mali, to represent President Uhuru Kenyatta at the 27th Africa&ndash;France Summit.The summit&rsquo;s agenda include peace, security and other issues, such as education, health, investment and Sustainable Development Goals.France uses the summit to explore areas in which it can support development in the continent.&ldquo;The President has just come from India, where he was working for the people of Kenya. He has now sent me to Mali to represent Kenya for more work,&rdquo; Ruto said yesterday in Kasarani during the launch of Jubilee Party membership smart cards.